Description: Electra MPC Guitar X930 Vulcan Charcoal Grey/ Brown Sunburst on mahogany body. Body resembles a Les Paul curved top with a "Tele" curve on the upper bout. Chrome hardware, small block inlays on fretboard, 2 humbuckers, naturally aged nickel plated. 5 position rotary switch, for tone, coil splitting etc. (similar to switches/ circuitry on an ES-345). Made between 1980 and 1983. This thing is a tone-monster, a beast. If you are looking, you (hopefully) know what this is. Used condition, some knicks, mainly on the back, bottom edge, near the module door. A “finish” crack in the neck (see it in the pictures), not a cracked neck…just a paint finish crack. Super nice(AAA+?) flamed, curved maple top. Set neck, will challenge any Gibson Les Paul guitar of that era! Pink/ Green true Mother of Pearl inlays. This is the sought after MPC (Module Powered Components) model. The modules are not included, available elsewhere on eBay. Tested the electronics with other modules I have: Cavity 1 works as it should, Cavity 2 may need some contact cleaning, not as responsive as it should be. Plays like a normal guitar without the modules, keep those switches "up" if not using modules. Transparent black/ brown,very flamey, color in the posting is quite accurate.. Comes with blue lined case,two broken latches. For more information: https://www.vintageguitar.com/4914/4914/
Title: Electra MPC Guitar,  X930 Vulcan, Beautiful Flame Top, Player Condition
